cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a latent variable model to learn numerical representations of game avatars that encode synergy and opposition relationships between pairs of avatars. This involves complex interactions between game avatars, which suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), social and information networks (cs.SI), or computation and language (cs.CL). However, since the focus is on learning numerical representations and downstream tasks such as match outcome prediction and avatar pick recommender, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories.
